BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Way of the Bow: Kyūdō\, Expression & Mindfulness
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260720T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260720T183000
DTSTAMP:20260709T122847Z
UID:dartmouth-groups-1630714@free-food-dartmouth
DESCRIPTION:Original event page(s):\nhttps://dartmouthgroups.dartmouth.edu
 /rsvp_boot?id=1630714\n\nDescription:\nImmerse yourself in mindfulness thr
 ough observing Kyūdō (Japanese archery) and experiencing the practices o
 f haiku and Shinrin-yoku (forest bathing)!\nKyūdō originated as a Samura
 i martial art in Japan and evolved into a mindfulness practice. Practicing
  kyūdō involves relaxing the body\, focusing attention\, and calming one
 ’s heart/mind for precise drawing of the bow and releasing the arrow. It
  is a path to opening one's heart and mind to the natural dignity of being
  human\, beyond the obstacles of ambition\, frustration\, and doubt.  Hitt
 ing the target is not considered as important as coordinating body\, mind\
 , and bow.\nYou are invited to interact with members of the local Blue Cli
 ff Kyudojo\, led by Ray Chin\, including Solomon Diamond D’97. You can a
 lso experience haiku writing alongside poet Keysi Montás\, shinrin-yoku (
 forest bathing) led by Belinda Chiu D’98\, and try Japanese tea and snac
 ks.\nCome for part of the time or stay for the entire expression!\n\nSpons
 or / organizer: Office of Pluralism and Leadership / Student Wellness Cent
 er at Dartmouth\n\nSource: Dartmouth Groups\n\nWhy this was included: food
  or meal keyword in title/summary\n\nFood availability is inferred from th
 e source listing\; verify details before attending.
LOCATION:Private Location (sign in to display)
STATUS:CONFIRMED
URL:https://dartmouthgroups.dartmouth.edu/rsvp_boot?id=1630714
END:VEVENT
